1238
01:29:29.168 --> 01:29:31.336
COSMO: That's great! Perfect. Cut.

1239
01:29:33.631 --> 01:29:36.630
Till the stars turn cold.

1240
01:29:37.051 --> 01:29:39.379
Oh, Kathy, I love you.

1241
01:29:41.347 --> 01:29:43.766
I can't wait till this
picture's finished.


1242
01:29:43.850 --> 01:29:47.429
No more secrecy. I'm gonna
let Lina and everyone know.


1243
01:29:47.437 --> 01:29:50.230
Your fans will be
bitterly disappointed.


1244
01:29:50.231 --> 01:29:54.152
From now on, there's only
one fan I'm worried about.


1245
01:29:57.363 --> 01:29:58.572
ZELDA: There!

1246
01:29:58.573 --> 01:30:01.902
- What did I tell you?
- Thanks, Zelda. You're a real pal.


1247
01:30:01.909 --> 01:30:06.080
I want that girl off the lot at once!
She ain't gonna be my voice.


1248
01:30:06.081 --> 01:30:07.873
Zelda told me everything.

1249
01:30:07.915 --> 01:30:10.914
- Thanks, Zelda. You're a real pal.
- Anytime, Don.


1250
01:30:10.918 --> 01:30:12.370
Look, Don and I...

1251
01:30:12.420 --> 01:30:15.294
Don! Don't you dare call him Don!

1252
01:30:15.298 --> 01:30:18.502
I was calling him Don
before you were born.


1253
01:30:18.551 --> 01:30:20.469
I mean... You were kissing him!

1254
01:30:20.553 --> 01:30:24.178
I was kissing her. I happen
to be in love with her.


1255
01:30:24.223 --> 01:30:28.435
That's ridiculous! Everybody
knows you're in love with me.


1256
01:30:28.436 --> 01:30:32.766
Ha, ha. Now look, Lina.
Try and understand this.


1257
01:30:32.774 --> 01:30:34.647
I'm going to marry her.

1258
01:30:34.734 --> 01:30:37.608
Silly boy. She ain't
the marrying kind.


1259
01:30:37.612 --> 01:30:40.656
She's a flirt trying to
get ahead by using you.


1260
01:30:40.698 --> 01:30:45.278
Well, I'll put a stop to that!
I'm gonna go up and see R.F. right now!


1261
01:30:45.286 --> 01:30:46.953
A little late.
The picture's finished.


1262
01:30:46.954 --> 01:30:49.498
If she weren't in it,
you'd be finished too.


1263
01:30:49.499 --> 01:30:52.669
As far as I can see, she's
the only one who's finished.


1264
01:30:52.752 --> 01:30:53.953
Who'll hear of her?

1265
01:30:53.961 --> 01:30:57.335
Everybody. Why do you think
Zelda's in such a sweat?


1266
01:30:57.340 --> 01:30:59.299
Kathy nearly stole the
picture from her.


1267
01:30:59.300 --> 01:31:01.580
She's only doing you a favor
in <i>The Dancing Cavalier.</i>


1268
01:31:01.636 --> 01:31:04.840
And she's getting full
screen credit for it too.


1269
01:31:04.931 --> 01:31:08.809
It'll say on the screen that I
don't talk and sing for myself?


1270
01:31:08.810 --> 01:31:10.933
Of course. What do you think?

1271
01:31:10.978 --> 01:31:13.180
- They can't do that.
- It's already done.


1272
01:31:13.272 --> 01:31:15.725
There's a whole publicity
campaign planned.


1273
01:31:15.817 --> 01:31:17.439
Publicity?

1274
01:31:17.485 --> 01:31:19.528
They can't make a fool out of me.

1275
01:31:19.529 --> 01:31:22.357
They can't make a laughingstock
out of Lina Lamont.


1276
01:31:22.448 --> 01:31:25.527
What do they think I am,
dumb or something?


1277
01:31:25.618 --> 01:31:28.071
Why, I make more money...

1278
01:31:28.663 --> 01:31:30.740
than Calvin Coolidge...

1279
01:31:30.790 --> 01:31:32.833
put together!

1280
01:31:34.669 --> 01:31:39.591
ROD: "Monumental Pictures enthusiastic
over Lina's singing and dancing."


1281
01:31:39.632 --> 01:31:40.841
I never said that.

1282
01:31:40.842 --> 01:31:45.047
"Premiere tomorrow night to reveal
Lina Lamont, big musical talent."


1283
01:31:45.054 --> 01:31:48.383
You can't pull a switch like this
on the publicity department.


1284
01:31:48.391 --> 01:31:50.719
We were prepared for
the Selden campaign.


1285
01:31:50.768 --> 01:31:53.019
Now you do this. At
least keep us informed.


1286
01:31:53.020 --> 01:31:56.019
Wait a minute. I don't
know anything about this.


1287
01:31:56.023 --> 01:31:57.475
What are we gonna do?

1288
01:31:57.483 --> 01:31:58.684
LINA: Nothing.

1289
01:31:59.485 --> 01:32:02.234
Absolutely nothing.

1290
01:32:02.321 --> 01:32:05.570
You wouldn't wanna call the
papers and say Lina Lamont...


1291
01:32:05.575 --> 01:32:08.073
is a big fat liar.

1292
01:32:08.161 --> 01:32:09.908
Did you send this stuff out?

1293
01:32:09.996 --> 01:32:13.540
I gave an exclusive story
to every paper in town.


1294
01:32:13.541 --> 01:32:15.914
You'll never get away
with it. Call the papers.


1295
01:32:15.918 --> 01:32:17.916
I wouldn't do that if I were you.

1296
01:32:17.920 --> 01:32:20.213
Don't tell me what to do, Lina.

1297
01:32:20.214 --> 01:32:23.918
What do you think I am,
dumb or something?


1298
01:32:23.926 --> 01:32:27.255
I had my lawyer go
over my contract.


1299
01:32:27.305 --> 01:32:28.597
Contract?

1300
01:32:28.681 --> 01:32:31.391
And I control my
publicity, not you.


1301
01:32:31.392 --> 01:32:32.767
- Yeah?
- Yeah.


1302
01:32:32.768 --> 01:32:36.017
The studio is responsible for
every word printed about me.


1303
01:32:36.022 --> 01:32:39.317
If I don't like it, I can sue.

1304
01:32:39.400 --> 01:32:40.647
What?

1305
01:32:40.693 --> 01:32:43.111
I can sue.

1306
01:32:43.112 --> 01:32:46.282
If you tell the papers
about Kathy Selden...


1307
01:32:46.324 --> 01:32:51.246
it would be "detrimental and
deleterious" to my career.


1308
01:32:51.704 --> 01:32:55.033
I could sue you for
the whole studio.


1309
01:32:55.082 --> 01:32:57.535
- That's a lot of nonsense.
- Says so.


1310
01:32:57.585 --> 01:32:59.162
Right here.

1311
01:32:59.253 --> 01:33:03.924
Contract dated June 8, 1925,
paragraph 34, subdivision letter A.


1312
01:33:03.925 --> 01:33:06.173
"The party of the first part..."

1313
01:33:06.219 --> 01:33:08.261
- That's me.
- You win, Lina.


1314
01:33:08.262 --> 01:33:11.090
We better take Kathy's
credit card off the screen.


1315
01:33:11.098 --> 01:33:12.641
All right, go ahead.

1316
01:33:12.642 --> 01:33:15.061
Let's just get this
premiere over with.


1317
01:33:15.102 --> 01:33:16.645
Satisfied?

1318
01:33:16.646 --> 01:33:19.349
There's just one little thing more.

1319
01:33:19.607 --> 01:33:23.857
You want me to change the name of
the studio to Lamont Pictures, Inc.?


1320
01:33:23.945 --> 01:33:26.112
R.F., you're cute.

1321
01:33:26.113 --> 01:33:28.156
Now, I was just thinking.

1322
01:33:28.157 --> 01:33:30.860
You've given her a part
in Zelda's picture...


1323
01:33:30.952 --> 01:33:33.655
and you'll give her a
bigger one in the next.


1324
01:33:33.746 --> 01:33:35.448
So, what?

1325
01:33:35.456 --> 01:33:38.375
If she's done such a grand
job doubling for my voice...


1326
01:33:38.459 --> 01:33:41.959
don't you think she ought
to go on doing just that?


1327
01:33:41.963 --> 01:33:44.461
- And nothing else.
- You're out of your mind.


1328
01:33:44.465 --> 01:33:47.714
I'm still more important
to the studio than she is.


1329
01:33:47.760 --> 01:33:49.720
I wouldn't do that to
her in a million years.


1330
01:33:49.762 --> 01:33:53.466
You'd take her career away.
People don't do things like that.


1331
01:33:53.474 --> 01:33:55.221
People?

1332
01:33:55.309 --> 01:33:57.352
I ain't people.

1333
01:33:57.436 --> 01:33:59.388
I am a...

1334
01:34:02.608 --> 01:34:07.153
"A shimmering, glowing star
in the cinema firmament."


1335
01:34:07.154 --> 01:34:09.197
It says so...

1336
01:34:09.323 --> 01:34:10.866
right there.

1337
01:34:23.170 --> 01:34:28.174
<i>Oh, Pierre, Pierre, my darling.
At last, I've found you.</i>


1338
01:34:28.175 --> 01:34:29.422
<i>Oh, Pierre.</i>

1339
01:34:29.468 --> 01:34:33.423
<i>Pierre, you're hurt.
Speak to me, speak to me.</i>


1340
01:34:34.056 --> 01:34:38.261
<i>(SINGIN)
I'll kiss her with a sigh.</i>


1341
01:34:38.853 --> 01:34:40.851
<i>Would you?</i>

1342
01:34:40.980 --> 01:34:43.023
<i>Would you?</i>

1343
01:34:43.316 --> 01:34:47.362
<i>And if the girl were I.</i>

1344
01:34:47.445 --> 01:34:49.192
<i>Would you?</i>

1345
01:34:49.530 --> 01:34:51.778
<i>Would you?</i>

1346
01:34:52.033 --> 01:34:55.533
<i>Oh, Pierre, hold me
in your arms always.</i>


1347
01:34:55.536 --> 01:34:57.033
Lockwood's a sensation.

1348
01:34:57.038 --> 01:35:00.913
Yes, but Lamont! What a voice!
Isn't she marvelous?


1349
01:35:01.000 --> 01:35:03.703
- It's going over wonderfully, isn't it?
- Yeah.


1350
01:35:03.711 --> 01:35:08.257
<i>Our love will last till
the stars turn cold.</i>


1351
01:35:08.716 --> 01:35:13.553
<i>(SINGING)
And would you dare to say.</i>


1352
01:35:13.554 --> 01:35:18.931
<i>Let's do the same as they.</i>

1353
01:35:20.186 --> 01:35:21.186
<i>I would.</i>

1354
01:35:25.399 --> 01:35:29.775
<i>Would you?</i>

1355
01:35:36.661 --> 01:35:39.114
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDS)

1356
01:35:53.386 --> 01:35:54.928
R.F., it's a real smash.

1357
01:35:54.929 --> 01:35:57.848
- Congratulations. We owe you a lot.
- Thank you.


1358
01:35:57.890 --> 01:35:59.967
- Kathy, we made it!
- It's a miracle!


1359
01:36:00.059 --> 01:36:02.011
It's great, Don. Just great.

1360
01:36:02.061 --> 01:36:05.140
You were fabulous. You sang
as well as Kathy Selden.


1361
01:36:05.147 --> 01:36:08.274
And I'm gonna for a long time.

1362
01:36:08.275 --> 01:36:09.476
What do you mean?

1363
01:36:09.527 --> 01:36:12.981
I mean she's gonna go
right on singing for me.


1364
01:36:13.072 --> 01:36:14.364
Listen, Lina.

1365
01:36:14.448 --> 01:36:18.323
I thought something was cooking
beneath those bleached curls.


1366
01:36:18.327 --> 01:36:21.656
Kathy has her own career.
She only did this for this picture.


1367
01:36:21.747 --> 01:36:23.324
That's what you think.

1368
01:36:23.332 --> 01:36:25.159
Come on, come on.

1369
01:36:25.251 --> 01:36:27.670
- Lina's getting carried away.
- Yeah, she is.


1370
01:36:27.753 --> 01:36:29.330
Listen, you boa constrictor.

1371
01:36:29.422 --> 01:36:32.375
Don't get any fancy ideas
about the future. Tell her!


1372
01:36:32.466 --> 01:36:35.010
Never mind, R.F.!
Listen to that applause.


1373
01:36:35.094 --> 01:36:36.887
Wait till the money rolls in.

1374
01:36:36.929 --> 01:36:41.054
You won't give all that up because
a nobody don't wanna be my voice.


1375
01:36:41.142 --> 01:36:43.265
She's got something.
It's a gold mine.


1376
01:36:43.310 --> 01:36:45.638
Part of that choice is mine.

1377
01:36:45.646 --> 01:36:47.143
And I just won't do it.

1378
01:36:47.148 --> 01:36:50.978
You've got a five-year contract.
You'll do what R.F. says.


1379
01:36:50.985 --> 01:36:53.688
What's the matter?
Why don't you tell her off?


1380
01:36:53.696 --> 01:36:55.773
I'm confused.
This thing is so big...


1381
01:36:55.823 --> 01:36:59.197
- They're tearing the house apart.
- Take a curtain call.


1382
01:36:59.201 --> 01:37:01.661
I once gave you a cigar.
Can I have it back?


1383
01:37:01.662 --> 01:37:05.207
Listen! I'm an avalanche!
Selden, you're stuck.


1384
01:37:05.291 --> 01:37:08.709
If this happens, get a new boy.
I won't stand for it.


1385
01:37:08.710 --> 01:37:12.336
Who needs you? They'd come to see
me if I played opposite a monkey!


1386
01:37:12.339 --> 01:37:13.882
Don's a smash too.

1387
01:37:13.966 --> 01:37:16.715
I'll say a few words.
I'm still running the studio.


1388
01:37:16.719 --> 01:37:18.386
I'm not so sure!

1389
01:37:18.387 --> 01:37:21.887
You're Mr. Producer, always
running things, running me.


1390
01:37:21.891 --> 01:37:25.561
From now on, as far as I'm
concerned, I'm running things.


1391
01:37:25.644 --> 01:37:28.142
- Lina Lamont Pictures, Inc., huh?
- Yeah.


1392
01:37:28.147 --> 01:37:30.065
You've gone a little too far.

1393
01:37:30.107 --> 01:37:32.560
